title: WikiText Syntax Sample
tags: Examples Reference

\define myMacro(param1, param2:"default value")
This is a macro with $param1$ and $param2$.
\end

\procedure myProcedure(name, count:1)
<$list filter="[range<count>]">
Hello <<name>>!
</$list>
\end

\function myFunction(input) [<input>addprefix[Result: ]]

\widget $my.widget(title)
<div class="my-widget">
<$transclude $variable="title"/>
</div>
\end

\rules only bold italic link

\import [[$:/core/macros/CSS]]

\parameters(width:100, height:200)

\whitespace trim

! Heading Level 1

This is a paragraph under heading 1. It contains ''bold text'', //italic text//, __underlined text__, ~~strikethrough~~, ^^superscript^^, ,,subscript,,, and @@highlighted text@@.

!! Heading Level 2

Here's some `inline code` and a [[Wiki Link]] and [[Link with custom text|Target Tiddler]].

!!! Heading Level 3

External links: [ext[TiddlyWiki|https://tiddlywiki.com]] and [ext[https://example.com]].

!!!! Heading Level 4

Image examples:
[img[https://example.com/image.png]]
[img width=200 [image.jpg]]
[img class="thumbnail" tooltip="A nice image" [picture.png]]
[img[Description|https://example.com/photo.jpg]]

!!!!! Heading Level 5

CamelCase links work too: HelloWorld, MyTiddler, WikiWord.

System links: $:/core/ui/ViewTemplate, $:/plugins/tiddlywiki/codemirror.

!!!!!! Heading Level 6

URL auto-links: https://tiddlywiki.com and mailto:test@example.com.

