!! Code Blocks

!!! Fenced Code Block (JavaScript)

```javascript
function greet(name) {
    console.log(`Hello, ${name}!`);
    return {
        message: "Welcome",
        timestamp: Date.now()
    };
}

greet("TiddlyWiki");
```

!!! Fenced Code Block (CSS)

```css
.my-component {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    background-color: #f0f0f0;
    padding: 1em;
    border-radius: 4px;
}

.my-component:hover {
    box-shadow: 0 2px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
}
```

!!! Fenced Code Block (TiddlyWiki)

```tiddlywiki
\define greeting(name)
Hello, $name$! Welcome to ''TiddlyWiki''.
\end

<<greeting "World">>
```

!!! Plain Code Block

```
This is a plain code block
without any language specified.
    It preserves whitespace.
```

